'''Helping Hands''' is a community in VRChat, is a unique initiative focused on bridging communication between Deaf, hard-of-hearing, and hearing individuals through immersive experiences in virtual reality. Originating as a small group aiming to connect Deaf players with other Deaf players, it has grown into a broader community with over 6,000 members globally<ref>As of Nov 2024</ref>. They primarily use VRChat and Discord to create a safe and supportive space for learning and socializing, often incorporating multiple sign languages, including ASL, BSL, JSL, KSL, LSF<ref>Acronyms for American Sign Language, British Sign Language, Japanese Sign Language, Korean Sign Language, and Langue des Signes Française (French Sign Language).</ref> and more.

